ABUJA (SundiataPost) – With the addition of 328 new COVID-19 cases on Friday, Nigeria’s total number of confirmed cases stands at 11,844. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released the update on Friday night.The new cases came from the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) and 13 states of the federation. Lagos, which is the epicentre of the virus reported 121 new cases. FCT has 70 cases while Bauchi and Rivers states recorded 25 and 18 respectively. The full report is as follows: 328 new cases of #COVID19; Lagos-121FCT-70Bauchi-25Rivers-18Oyo-16Kaduna-15Gombe-14Edo-13Ogun-13Jigawa-8Enugu-6Kano-5Osun-2Ondo-2 11844 cases of #COVID19NigeriaDischarged: 3696Deaths: 333 Nigeria on Friday night confirmed five new cases of Covid-19, bringing the number to 70. According to Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, tweeting via @NCDCgov:  “Five new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 3 in FCT & 2 in Oyo State “As at 08:00 pm 27th March there… March 27, 2020 In "News" Osun and Ogun states have recorded three and one new cases of Covid-19 respectively as total for Nigeria now stands at 135. Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, announced this Tuesday morning via its official twitter handle @NCDCgov. The tweet reads: “Four new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in… March 31, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - Nigeria has again recorded eight new cases of coronavirus, also know as Covid-19, bringing the total number to 97. Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, Saturday night announced that Oyo State recorded four new cases while Kaduna has been added to the list. The tweet @NCDCgov reads: “Eight… March 28, 2020 In "News"